{"id":"2012.03187","submitter":"Younjin Kim","authors":"Younjin Kim","title":"The number of $k$-dimensional corner-free subsets of grids","comments":"21 pages","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.CO","license":"http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/","abstract":"  A subset $A$ of the $k$-dimensional grid $\\{1,2, \\cdots, N\\}^k$ is called\n$k$-dimensional corner-free if it does not contain a set of points of the form\n$\\{ a \\} \\cup \\{ a + de_i : 1 \\leq i \\leq k \\}$ for some $a \\in \\{1,2, \\cdots,\nN\\}^k$ and $d > 0$, where $e_1,e_2, \\cdots, e_k$ is the standard basis of\n$\\mathbb{R}^k$. We define the maximum size of a $k$-dimensional corner-free\nsubset of $\\{1,2, \\cdots, N\\}^k$ by $c_k(N)$. In this paper, we show that the\nnumber of $k$-dimensional corner-free subsets of the $k$-dimensional grid\n$\\{1,2, \\cdots, N\\}^k$ is at most $2^{O(c_k(N))}$ for infinitely many values of\n$N$. Our main tool for the proof is a supersaturation result for\n$k$-dimensional corners in sets of size $\\Theta(c_k(N))$ and the hypergraph\ncontainer method.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 6 Dec 2020 05:46:56 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 3 Mar 2022 06:35:41 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-04"}
